quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
43,11,"He Who sent down water from the sky in a determined measure, {1} and thereby We revived a dead land: likewise will you be raised up (from the earth) {2} �",footnotes:1:Here
43,12,"He Who created these pairs, {1} all of them, and provided you ships and cattle on which you ride,",footnotes:1:Pairs here does not imply only pairs of men and women among human beings and of males and females among animals and vegetation
43,13,"so that when you are mounted upon them you may remember the bounty of your Lord, and say: “Glory be to Him Who has subjected this to Us whereas we did not have the strength to subdue it. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
43,14,"It is to our Lord that we shall eventually return.” {1}",footnotes:1:That is
43,15,"Yet they have made some of His servants a part of Him. {1} Indeed man is most evidently thankless.",footnotes:1:“Assign to some of His slaves a share with Him” implies declaring a servant of Allah His offspring
43,16,"Has Allah taken for Himself daughters out of those whom He creates and has chosen you to have sons? {1}",footnotes:1:Here
43,17,"(They believe so although when) any of them is given tidings of the birth of a female child the like of which he assigns to the Merciful One, his countenance darkens and he is choked with grief."
43,18,"Do they assign to Allah one who grows up amidst ornaments and is not well-versed in the art of disputation? {1}",footnotes:1:In other words
43,19,"They claim that angels, who are Allah's chosen servants, {1} are females. Did they witness how their body is constituted? {2} Their testimony shall be written and they shall be called to account.",footnotes:1:That is
43,20,"They say: “Had the Merciful One so willed, we would never have worshipped these deities.” {1} But they have no knowledge of the matter and are simply conjecturing.",footnotes:1:This was their reasoning from destiny to cover up their deviation and error
43,21,"Or did We bestow upon them a Book before on whose authority they are holding on (to angel-worship)? {1}",footnotes:1:It means this: These ignorant people think that whatever is happening in the world has the approval of Allah for it
43,22,"Nay; they simply claim: “We found our forefathers on a way, and we continue to find guidance in their footsteps.” {1}",footnotes:1:That is
